---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Research Use Cases"
  description="See how CodeArmy fits AI4Science and long-running research optimization workflows."
>
  <section class="container page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Research Use Cases</p>
    <h1>Designed for coding plus experiments, not code alone.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      CodeArmy is especially well suited to long-running research workflows where code changes,
      experiment runs, metrics, cluster jobs, and reports all need to move together.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="container page-body grid-2">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>JUNO Monte Carlo parameter tuning</h3>
      <p>
        Treat Monte Carlo parameter optimization as a campaign with hypotheses, scheduled runs,
        metrics, reviews, and evidence-backed summaries.
      </p>
      <ul class="page-list">
        <li>Track candidate parameter sets and observed improvements.</li>
        <li>Keep cluster runs tied to the same campaign state.</li>
        <li>Generate phase summaries for group discussion and follow-up decisions.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>CEPC fast-simulation DiT optimization</h3>
      <p>
        Manage model architecture changes, training runs, speed-quality tradeoffs, and evaluation
        results with a single repo-first workflow.
      </p>
      <ul class="page-list">
        <li>Compare model variants across metrics, resources, and experimental evidence.</li>
        <li>Use review gates before adopting a new baseline.</li>
        <li>Turn experiment outcomes into durable reports, not ephemeral chat notes.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
